cat — concatenate files to standard output

SYNOPSIS
  cat [FILE...]

DESCRIPTION
  Reads each FILE in order and writes the contents to stdout. Without
  arguments, reads from stdin. Paths are resolved through k.vfs, so you
  can read /proc/<pid>/* and /dev/<component>/* synthetic entries the
  same way as regular files.

EXAMPLES
  cat /etc/motd                 the message-of-the-day
  cat /var/log/dmesg.log | grep error
  cat < input.txt               redirect stdin
